<h2>The weather in August 2020</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
In August, average temperatures were higher than the 1981-2010 average for August over large parts of Europe, with 'exceptionally above average' mean but also minimum temperatures occurring especially over central and eastern Europe. Largest mean and maximum temperature anomalies occured over Germany and the Benelux countries with values between 2 and 3 &#176;C (see also event description above).
